column2: Data for particles in composite halos (all halos with same number of np=80). This can be used to compute density, mean flow and dispersion in composite halos

column1:
r: Distance of particle 
to halo center (Mpc/h)
column2:
r2: Distance of particle to 
halo axis of rotation (Mpc/h)
column3:
ur: Particle velocity of 
peculiar radial flow (km/s)
column4:
ur2: Particle velocity of radial flow 
including Hubble flow (km/s)
column5:
ut1: Particle velocity of 
azimuthal flow (km/s)
column6:
ut2: Particle velocity of 
polar flow (km/s)
column7:
Phi: Particle total potential 
from both intra- and 
inter-halo interaction (km^2/s^2)
column8:
Phi_v: Particle potential from 
intra-halo interaction (km^2/s^2)
